ai_endpoints_token_intro: You need to generate API keys to use AI Endpoints. They will automatically be linked to a user and your Public Cloud project’s access policy (IAM).
ai_endpoints_token_success_message: Your API key has been generated. You can only view it once. Please remember to copy and back it up securely.
ai_endpoints_token_deletion_message: Are you sure you want to delete the API key?
ai_endpoints_token_name_error: This key name is already taken
ai_endpoints_token_name_required: You have to name the key
ai_endpoints_token_invalid_format: The key name must not contain spaces or special characters
ai_endpoints_token_expiration_date: Set expiry date for API key
ai_endpoints_token_discovery_mod: Your Public Cloud project is currently in ‘Discovery’ mode. To use AI Endpoints, activate your project by adding a payment method. This lets you generate your first API key to begin using the service.
ai_endpoints_non_admin_user: You must have Administrator status to be able to manipulate API keys
